<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net">
  <diagram id="uedDBjp-Z_iSIwonFi2j" name="Page-1">
    <mxGraphModel dx="4225" dy="3625" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1654" pageHeight="2336" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{&quot;data&quot;:&quot;@startuml\ntitle Hospital Management System\n\n&#39; --- Core Identity Domain ---\nclass User {\n    +userId: Long\n    +username: String\n    +password: String\n    +email: String\n    +phone: String {Encrypted}\n    +role: String\n    +auth: boolean {Verified Status}\n    +isFrozen: boolean\n    +permissions: Set&lt;String&gt;\n    --\n    +login()\n    +signup()\n    +logout()\n}\n\nnote left of User\n  **Rule: Account Safety**\n  -- Every user needs a unique email and valid credentials.\n  context User inv \&quot;Account require a unique email\&quot;:\n    User.allInstances()-&gt;isUnique(email), self.username.size() &gt; 0 and self.password.size() &gt; 0\n\n  -- Administrative Control\n  -- Frozen accounts lose all system permissions immediately.\n  context User inv \&quot;Frozen accounts are restricted from all actions\&quot;:\n    self.isFrozen = true implies self.permissions-&gt;isEmpty()\nend note\n\n&#39; --- Clinical Domain ---\nclass Doctor {\n    +id: Long\n    +specialization: String\n    +rating: float\n    +bio: String\n    +certificates: List&lt;String&gt;\n    --\n    +updateBio()\n    +reviewPatientHistory()\n    +listAppointment()\n    +makeAvailableTime()\n}\n\nnote right of Doctor\n  **Rule: Professional Vetting**\n  -- Doctors cannot practice or set schedules until they provide \n  their certificates and receive Admin verification.\n  context Doctor inv \&quot;Verification requires certificates and Admin approval\&quot;:\n    self.certificates-&gt;notEmpty() and (self.auth = true implies self.canManageSchedule())\nend note\n\nclass Patient {\n    +id: Long\n    +history: historyD\n    --\n    +viewDoctorDetails()\n    +listDoctors()\n    +makeAppointment()\n    +rate()\n    +viewHistory()\n    +makeHistory()\n}\n\n&#39; --- Medical &amp; Scheduling Support ---\nclass historyD {\n    +id: Long\n    +history: String\n    +note: String\n    +patient: Patient\n}\n\nclass Appointment {\n    +id: Long\n    +availabilitySlot: Long\n    +note: String\n    +patientName: String\n    +doctorName: String\n    +patientId: Long\n    +doctorId: Long\n    +date: Date\n    +timeSlot: String\n    +phoneNumber: String\n}\n\nnote bottom of Appointment\n  **Rule: Booking Integrity**\n  -- One time slot, one patient. Prevents medical double-booking.\n  context Appointment inv \&quot;Double-booking a single time slot is prohibited\&quot;:\n    Appointment.allInstances()-&gt;isUnique(availabilitySlot)\n\n  -- Patients can only manage their own medical bookings.\n  context Appointment inv \&quot;Patients may only manage their own appointments\&quot;:\n    self.patientId = currentUser.id\nend note\n\n\nclass AvailabilitySlot {\n    +id: Long\n    +days: List&lt;String&gt;\n    +startTime: LocalTime\n    +endTime: LocalTime\n    +durationMinutes: int\n}\n\nclass Admin {\n    --\n    +deleteUser()\n    +verifyDoctor()\n    +freezeAccount()\n    +unfreezeUser()\n    +listUsers()\n    +listDoctorsWantVerify()\n}\n\n\n&#39; --- Structural Links ---\nUser &lt;|-- Patient\nUser &lt;|-- Doctor\nUser &lt;|-- Admin\nPatient \&quot;1\&quot; *-- \&quot;1\&quot; historyD\nDoctor \&quot;1\&quot; -- \&quot;*\&quot; AvailabilitySlot\nAppointment \&quot;*\&quot; -- \&quot;1\&quot; AvailabilitySlot\nPatient \&quot;1\&quot; -- \&quot;*\&quot; Appointment : \&quot;books\&quot;\nDoctor \&quot;1\&quot; -- \&quot;*\&quot; Appointment : \&quot;attends\&quot;\n\n@enduml\n&quot;,&quot;format&quot;:&quot;svg&quot;}" id="OyADFi8Tq_fXoBviTkyV-115">
          <mxCell parent="1" style="shape=image;noLabel=1;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1">
            <mxGeometry height="978" width="1259" x="-1630" y="-2270" as="geometry" />
          </mxCell>
        </UserObject>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
